##"sudden death of a doctor after work is not recognized as a work injury" , the final result

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Zhang Wei / Legal Daily

Dr. ICYANG PAROD's sudden death at home, which has drawn public attention for days, was not ruled an industrial accident, and the final result was announced recently.

On March 7, the Xiantao Bureau of Social Welfare in Hubei Province reversed a previous decision not to recognize work-related injuries and decided to re-classify Icyang Parod's death as a work-related injury in the event of a sudden illness that occurred in the course of epidemic prevention and preparedness.

Legal Daily reporter learned that behind this change is the administrative reconsideration decision made by the Xiantao Government of the People's Republic of China on March 6: To rescind the "decision not to recognize work-related injury" made by the Xiantao People's bureau, and ordered the agency to make a new decision within 60 days. The Xiantao Department of Justice is the Administrative Review Body for the city of Xiantao.

Family: died fighting pneumonia

ICYANG PAROD is an out-patient physician at the Sanfutan Township Health Center in Xiantao, Hubei Province.

In this anti-epidemic of the National War, as a medical staff and in the "hard hit areas" of his nature is an indisputable retrograde.

But before the final victory, the doctor, born in 1970, died. The death came so suddenly that no one expected him to see his colleagues again after he left work on February 12.

In the early hours of February 13, he developed chest pain, shortness of breath and other symptoms. He died despite emergency treatment. The medical certificate of Resident Death (inference) states that the cause of death is diagnosed as "acute myocardial infarction. ".

The time of departure was during non working hours and the place of departure was at home, but in the eyes of the family, ICYANG PAROD died fighting a new outbreak of pneumonia and should be considered an industrial injury.

"although not at the expense of his working hours and workplace, during this period his working hours and workplace have been extended to his home, meeting the requirements of the relevant provisions of the Work Injury Insurance Ordinance, " ICYANG PAROD's family said.

In this holiday free Spring Festival, they saw that Icyang Parod was still working overtime, and even when he got home, there were phone calls and other work.

In fact, the Xiantao Health Commission issued an emergency notice on January 22, medical and health units are required to "fully activate the wartime duty and standby mechanism, all personnel cancel the Spring Festival vacation, work according to normal working and rest time, strict implementation of the 24-hour duty system. ".

In addition, ICYANG PAROD's family did not rule out that ICYANG PAROD had a high probability of dying from the new pneumonia, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security of the People's Republic of China, the Ministry of Finance and the National Health Board should be considered for application of the circular on the protection of medical and related personnel who contract COVID-19 pneumonia in the performance of their duties.

The sanfutan health center, where ICYANG Parod lived, also believed that ICYANG Parod died during the "wartime state" of epidemic prevention and control, and should not mechanically determine the working time and place, or understand the legal terms. ICYANG PAROD's death was due to overwork, which should be considered an industrial injury.

On February 19, ICYANG PAROD's family went to the Xiantao Social Welfare Bureau with the relevant materials, hoping to identify ICYANG Parod as an industrial injury.

Bureau of Social Welfare: The case of death does not meet the statutory conditions

However, the Xiantao Bureau of Social Welfare issued the next day, "do not recognize industrial injury decision" , but gave a different conclusion.

Why not? The reason of the Xiantao Bureau of Social Affairs is that ICYANG PAROD did not undertake the duty of first-line epidemic prevention for some time before his death, working hours are relatively fixed, regular commuting to and from work, the time of ICYANG PAROD's sudden illness is in the early morning, the place is his home, it does not conform to the situation in which an injury due to an accident at work during working hours and in the workplace should be recognized as an injury at work. In addition, myocardial infarction does not fall within the scope of prescribed occupational diseases. As a result, ICYANG PAROD's death is not covered by section 14 of the Industrial Injury Insurance Act.

ICYANG PAROD's illness broke out in his home in the early hours of the morning, apparently not in the course of his work, and did not meet the statutory conditions for "working hours and jobs" , therefore, ICYANG PAROD's sudden death due to illness is not regarded as a work injury as stipulated in Article 15 of the Regulations on work injury insurance.

"although ICYANG PAROD was one of the most beautiful reversers of the current epidemic as a member of the medical staff, his professionalism is worthy of our respect and his tragic death is regrettable. However, as a executive branch, it is our duty to administer the work injury in accordance with the law. As the circumstances of his death do not meet the above statutory conditions for the recognition of work injury, we have accordingly made the decision not to recognize the work injury."according to the Xiantao People's Bureau, the above-mentioned facts are clear, the evidence is conclusive and the legal basis for application is correct.

GOVERNMENT: Working Hours should not be defined mechanically

The decision not to recognize an injury at work also gave ICYANG PAROD's family new hope for relief.

According to the article, those who are not satisfied with the decision on the determination of work-related injury May, within 60 days from the date of receiving the written decision, apply to the Xiantao Government of the People's Republic of China or the Hubei Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security for administrative reconsideration, or bring an administrative action directly to the Xiantao Municipal People's Court within six months.

On February 27, the Sanfutan Health Center, where ICYANG Parod lived, filed an application for reconsideration with the Government of the People's Republic of China of Xiantao. The Judicial Bureau of Xiantao, as the administrative reconsideration organ of the Xiantao government, officially accepted the case on the same day, iCYANG PAROD's family was involved as a third person.

With the administrative review, ICYANG PAROD's anti epidemic workload has further surfaced. Xiantao government, January 24, Sanfutan Township Health Center set up fever clinic expert Guidance Group, Icyang Parod as deputy head and responsible for day-to-day work, in addition to their own work, also involved in fever patients. From January 12 to February 12, ICYANG Parod treated 3,506 outpatients, including 670 patients with fever. During the epidemic, the hospital also announced Icyang Parod's phone number in the fever clinic, ICYANG PAROD did have rest time through the phone, Wechat to receive patient inquiries.

It is worth noting that the city government of Xiantao also confirmed the fact that Icyang Parod came to work with illness: on May 8,2017, ICYANG PAROD was hospitalized for 7 days in the First People's Hospital of Xiantao for diseases such as dilated cardiomyopathy and stage III hypertension. On January 30,2020, due to right chest pain, accompanied by chest tightness, asthma and other symptoms, the hospital sent a car to Xiantao First People's Hospital for examination. After the examination, ICYANG Parod continued to work with illness until his sudden death.

The XIANTAO government believes that in the context of a first-level response to a major public health emergency, the Sanfutan Township Health Center requires all its medical staff to be on standby 24 hours a day, and that doctors'mobile phone numbers should be posted at fever clinics, in favor of the implementation of patient consultation, Icyang Parod worked after there is indeed a case of receiving consultation by phone. ICYANG Parod treated 3,506 people between January 12 and February 12 and took part in the epidemic prevention work. Although the time of death was in the early morning of the 13th, the time of onset was after work on the 12th, it may be concluded that the death of the employee belongs to the circumstances of the death caused by a sudden illness occurring at work during working hours or at work, and that the circumstances of the death are consistent with Article 15, paragraph 1(1) , of the Regulations on work-related Injury Insurance, which "shall be regarded as work-related injuries" .

"ICYANG PAROD's work-related injury determination should take into account the working conditions during the special period of the epidemic, and should not mechanically define 'working hours' and 'working positions, ' " the Xiantao Government of the People's Republic of China said.

The XIANTAO government revoked the decision not to declare an industrial injury made by the Xiantao Social Welfare Bureau and ordered it to make a new decision within 60 days. On March 7, the Xiantao Bureau of Social Welfare made a decision to identify (or treat) ICYANG Parod's death as a work-related injury due to a sudden illness in the course of epidemic prevention and preparedness.

"The dust has finally settled, and I hope we can comfort my father's soul in heaven, and please rest assured, " ICYANG Parod's son, Liu Hang, said in a message posted on a friend's circle.
